        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>parsley & tarragon pesto</strong>, <strong>mayo </strong>and <strong>grated cheese </strong>in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy tarragon filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/re-nourish-chicken-soup-with-tarragon-cheese-toastie/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Divide the <strong>cheesy tarragon filling</strong> between the<strong> ciabatta base[s] </strong>and<strong> </strong>spread almost to the edges, leaving a small border</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/re-nourish-chicken-soup-with-tarragon-cheese-toastie/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top with a<strong> ciabatta lid</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>cheese & tarragon toastie[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/re-nourish-chicken-soup-with-tarragon-cheese-toastie/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> cheese & tarragon toastie[s] </strong>and cover with a smaller pan</p><p>Add a heavy weight (e.g. several tins) to the top pan and cook for 4-5 min per side, checking occasionally or until the ciabatta is golden and the cheese has melted</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? Use 2 pans or you may need to do this in batches!</p>",
